The paper deals with an online optimization problem involving a knapsack with a capacity constraint. This problem is a classic topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the performance of the proposed algorithms. The use of optimization techniques and analysis of algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the problem of managing capacity in modern applications such as wireless networks and cloud computing suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
